+{"id":"bd-6c20l","title":"FIBMAP must report unwritten extents as holes (return 0)","description":"FIBMAP currently returns the physical block number for FIEMAP_EXTENT_UNWRITTEN (preallocated, no data) extents. Linux ext4_bmap delegates to iomap_bmap which returns 0 for IOMAP_UNWRITTEN — so userspace tools (filefrag -B, e2image) treating unwritten regions as data when they should appear as holes. Fix: in dispatch_ioctl FIBMAP branch, when the matching extent has flags & FIEMAP_EXTENT_UNWRITTEN, return 0 (same as the hole path) instead of the physical block. Add regression test using IoctlRecordingFs / fiemap fixture that returns an UNWRITTEN extent at the queried block and asserts FIBMAP returns 0.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cod-fs","created_at":"2026-04-26T04:18:46.118833167Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T04:42:22.034726733Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T04:42:22.032804365Z","close_reason":"Fixed FIBMAP unwritten extent hole mapping and added direct dispatch coverage","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
